cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper discusses sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning methods, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of social media data and the focus on feature generation and selection suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of emoticons and slang expressions, which could be relevant to the study of online communication and cyberculture, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category as well.
